Fix fd-slicer stream API compatibility with Node.js v18+

fd-slicer's ReadStream and WriteStream used a manual 'destroyed' flag and
custom destroy() methods that conflict with the destroyed getter/setter
Node.js added to stream.Readable/Writable in v18. In Node.js v24 this causes
push(null) to be silently ignored, deadlocking inflate pipelines during electron
binary extraction. This applies the fix from:
https://github.com/andrewrk/node-fd-slicer/pull/5

